com.rti.dds.example.file
Class BlockingQueue

java.lang.Object
  com.rti.dds.example.file.BlockingQueue
public class BlockingQueue
extends java.lang.Object

This class provides queue functionality. The push and pop methods are blocking (hence, the name). This queue also has the option to limit the number of objects stored in the queue.

Method Detail

push

public void push(java.lang.Object o)
Push an Object into the queue. If the queue is full, this method will wait indefinitely for space before it returns.

Parameters:
o - The Object to be queued.

push

public boolean push(java.lang.Object o,
                    long timeout)
Push an Object into the queue. If the queue is full and the timeout expires, the Object will not be added and the return value will be false. If the queue is full at first, then space becomes available before timeout then the Object will be added and the return value will be true.

Parameters:
o - The Object to be queued.
timeout - The amount of time to block (in milliseconds) waiting for space in the queue.
Returns:
true if o was inserted into the queue, false otherwise.

clear

public void clear()

full

public boolean full()
This method checks whether or not the queue is full (at maximum capacity).

Returns:
true if the queue is full, false othewise.

pop

public java.lang.Object pop()
Get the next item from the queue. This method will block indefinitely while waiting for an item to become available if the queue is empty.

Returns:
The next item from the queue.

pop

public java.lang.Object pop(long timeout)
Get the next item from the queue. If the queue is empty, this method will wait for timeout milliseconds for an item to become available. If timeout is 0, this method waits indefinitely.

Parameters:
timeout - The number of milliseconds to wait for an item to become available.
Returns:
The next item from the queue or null if the queue was empty and the timeout expired.

empty
